<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,366,461]" box="[160,409,366,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,366,461]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Shell narrow, elongated, conical, back end slightly curved, smooth. Parapodia transparent, large, with double-axe shape.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="290" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1155,521,616]" box="[160,252,521,547]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1155,521,616]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Found in open waters close to the surface and around other pelagic pteropod and salp species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="290" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1155,676,840]" box="[160,300,676,702]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,676,702]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1155,676,840]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">
Cosmopolitan. In the Mediterranean Sea this species has been reported from the eastern and western Mediterranean, and in the 
<collectingCountry box="[679,742,746,771]" name="Malta" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Malta</collectingCountry>
stretch and between Mallorca and Sicily (
<bibRefCitation author="OBIS" box="[230,348,780,805]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290" pagination="22" refId="ref21226" refString="OBIS. 2021. Ocean Biogeographic Information System. Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO. Accessed 2021 May 22. www. iobis. org" type="journal article" year="2021">OBIS 2021</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first report of this species from the Mediterranean Spanish coast.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="290" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1155,900,1203]" box="[160,262,900,926]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,900,926]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1155,900,1203]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">
Almost all records in the Mediterranean are based on shell observations or from specimens caught in plankton tows in open waters, at superficial (
<quantity box="[855,942,970,995]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="290" unit="m" value="5.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="0.0">0–10 m</quantity>
) or greater depths (
<quantity box="[166,295,1004,1029]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="290" unit="m" value="650.0" valueMax="700.0" valueMin="600.0">600–700 m</quantity>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="OBIS" box="[307,422,1004,1029]" pageId="25" pageNumber="290" pagination="22" refId="ref21226" refString="OBIS. 2021. Ocean Biogeographic Information System. Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO. Accessed 2021 May 22. www. iobis. org" type="journal article" year="2021">OBIS 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Our specimens were found from February to March along with the massive arrival of pelagic zooplankton in superficial waters. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Eschscholtz, 1829" authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" box="[191,496,1074,1099]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Cyerce" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="25" pageNumber="290" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conica">
<emphasis box="[191,290,1074,1099]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">C. conica</emphasis>
Eschscholtz, 1829
</taxonomicName>
, so several specimens with slightly different morphologies have been collected to determine whether both species could be present. In the case of both species, this record represents the first observation of either taxon for the 
<collectingRegion box="[1071,1155,1143,1168]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="25" pageNumber="290">Catalan</collectingRegion>
coast.
</paragraph>
